href="erct-0010.xml"
addr="erct-0010"
title="Path object">path object</fr:link>. Any <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0031.xml"
addr="erct-0031"
title="Left cleaving of a family of path objects">left-cloven family of path objects</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}\colon    \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {} \to  \mathsf {PathObj}]]></fr:tex> gives rise to a canonical <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0012.xml"
addr="erct-0012"
title="Displayed path object">displayed path object</fr:link> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {A}]]></fr:tex> in which:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\colon  x\approx _{\mathcal {A}} y]]></fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\approx _{\mathcal {B}}^{p} b']]></fr:tex> to be <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p_*b \approx _{\mathcal {B} y} b']]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
 <fr:li>for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {} ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {B} x\right \rvert \mathclose {} ]]></fr:tex>, the identity element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {B}}{x}\colon  b \approx _{\mathcal {B}}^{\mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}{x}}b]]></fr:tex> is given by the component <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Phi _{\mathcal {B}} xb\colon    \mathopen {}\left \lparen \mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}{x}\right \rparen \mathclose {} _*b\approx _{\mathcal {B} x}{b}]]></fr:tex> of the unit law of the given right cleaving of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
 
   
